Jakadan Amurka ya zargi kasar Sin da cin zarafin tallace-tallace
Wata mako bayan wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani sanarwa a cikin wata jaridar Amurka mai dauke da labaran da ke nuna amfanin da kasashen biyu ke samu daga cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin ya zargi Beijing da amfani da kafafen yada labarai na Amurka wajen yada labaran.
A ranar Laraba da ta gabata, shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi magana game da wani shafin da aka biya na Tea Daily a De Moyne Register - jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a Iowa - bayan da ya zargi China da tsoma baki a zaben Amurka na ranar 6 ga Nuwamba, China ta musanta zargin.
Zargin da Trump ya yi cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna cewa jami'an tsaro na Amurka sun shiga tsakani da Reuters, wani sabon mataki a yakin neman zaben Washington na matsa lamba kan kasar Sin.
Duk da yake yana da kyau gwamnatocin kasashen waje su buga tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington , a halin yanzu suna cikin yakin kasuwanci inda suke daidaita harajin shigo da kayayyaki da juna.
Kudaden fansa da kasar Sin ta yi a farkon yakin cinikayya sun kai ga masu fitar da kayayyaki daga jihohin tarayya kamar Iowa, wadanda ke goyon bayan Jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, masana na kasar Sin da na Amurka sun tabbatar.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, mai shekaru da yawa, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing na cutar da ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kuma 'yan kasuwa.
Kasar Sin, in ji Branstad a cikin wata wasiƙa a cikin jaridar De Moyne Register, ta ninka yawan cin zarafin da ake yi wa 'yan jarida a cikin jaridarmu.
A cikin yada labaran, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi amfani da al'adun Amurka na 'yancin magana da kuma kafofin watsa labarai ta hanyar sanya tallace-tallace a cikin De Moyne Register in ji Branstad.
"A akasin haka, a cikin gidan jaridu na kusa da nan, a nan Beijing, za ka iya samun ra'ayoyi da yawa kawai kuma ba za ka ga ainihin abin da mutanen China ke tunani ba game da matsalar tattalin arzikin kasar Sin, domin kafofin watsa labarai suna ƙarƙashin iko na jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin", ya rubuta.
Ya kara da cewa, wata jarida mafi karbuwa a kasar Sin ta ki amincewa da shi a buga shi a cikin shafin, duk da cewa bai bayyana wane jarida yake ba.
